instance: A dull head between windy spaces.
A fine, pedantic sun in a satin waistcoat
A silence pervades the story, and a softness in the narrator's eye
And painful must be the storm
But through the pale, thin water Non-offensive feet still shine
For every lamppost I pass Beats like a fatalistic drum
Hope is the feathered thing that perches in the soul, and sings the melody without the words, and never stops altogether.
I don't care that beauty is mute
I have heard it in the coldest land
The heart of the ocean too soft, too blue

Reminiscence comes
Of dried geraniums without sun
The yellow mist brushing against the window panes
Yellow smoke rubbing its snout on window panes
Under a windy knob.
Where worried bodies of drowned men drift down in the green silence
a crow that flies in the sweetest air of the sky
a woman's face hand-painted by nature
like sweet rains to the ground
hiding your bravery in its rotting smoke
silenced the shrinking seas
kissing with a golden face the green meadows
the beauty of my sweet love
sometime too hot shines the eye of the sky
that sweet smell
the floors of silent seas.
the sessions of sweet silent thought
the wide world and all its vanished sweets
its substance still lives sweet
hearing with the eyes belongs to the fine wit of love
your sweet semblance to some other to give
